<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,572]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Etymology. This species is named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blahnik &amp; Holzenthal" authorityYear="2011" box="[587,706,476,500]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Mortoniella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acauda">
<emphasis box="[587,706,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">M. acauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, without a tail, from the Latin word 
<emphasis box="[1114,1182,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">cauda</emphasis>
or tail and referring to the absence of a narrow, ventromesal projection from the fused inferior appendages, which characterizes the group of species to which it appears to be most closely related.
</paragraph>
